I also worry about his health, as he was identified as having a presently undiagnosible genetic condition. It doesn't affect him much now but it strikes me as something somewhat troubling that may strike suddenly in the future.    To some degree I worry about all of my children in terms of social development. I want them to be honest and virtuous, and they often do things like steal or hit or lie that make me fear they may not develop virtue properly.    Along with that, I fear the influence of the technology of the day on my kids. We do a lot to limit "screen time," but I want my kids to not be addicted to devices. I'm not sure I model that well, especially as devices are so key to work in adult life.    I fear in the longer term the threat of video games ruining my kids' lives. I know so many 20 and 30-somethings who are wrecked by them. And I fear pornography and all the people on the net who would want to push that stuff towards them.
